# Spaceship Titanic - Project Description

## Overview

The "Spaceship Titanic" project aims to analyze the dataset of passengers onboard the Spaceship Titanic and build a classification model to predict whether a passenger survived the disaster or not. The dataset contains various features related to passengers, such as age, room service, food court, spa usage, VR deck usage, home planet, cryo sleep, destination, VIP status, etc.

The project will involve data preprocessing, exploratory data analysis (EDA), and building machine learning models using three different algorithms - XGBoost, LightGBM, and CatBoost. The best hyperparameters for each model will be determined using GridSearchCV and Optuna. The final model's performance will be evaluated based on accuracy, precision, recall, F1 score, and ROC AUC.
